                  </hi>. I live in Sloane-street, Chelsea, and am a watch-maker. On the 10th of April the prisoner came and asked to be shown a watch at about 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. or 4<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.—I had not got one, but I showed him a patent lever one at 6<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he seemed to approve of it, and said, "Lay it on one side"—he then asked to look at some guards—we showed him some—he chose one which was 30<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., but we said, as he had had the watch, he should have it for 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.—he then said, "Let me have a note for the watch"—before I could take up the pen, he ran off with the watch, and I after him—the policeman caught him in William-street with it.</p>
